w%2F118301662.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Faustralia-to-ban-foreign-investors-from-buying-existing-homes-for-two-years%2Famp_articleshow%2F118301662.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Families%20heartbreak%20after%20deadly%20Dehli%20railway%20station%20crush%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739702237000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F02cf%2Flive%2Fc6871340-ec4e-11ef-b5bb-0326be6bf9eb.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcn8x3kjd7zzo%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eyewitnesses%20and%20relatives%20of%20victims%20spoke%20of%20their%20pain%20and%20trauma%20after%20a%20crush%20at%20an%20overcrowded%20railway%20station%20claimed%2018%20lives.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcn8x3kjd7zzo%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcn8x3kjd7zzo.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcn8x3kjd7zzo.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI-enabled%20satellites%20could%20help%20the%20US%20evade%20a%20crippling%20cyber%20attack%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Radio%20telescopes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a5e03dbfebcc4d029e268c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERadio%20telescopes%20pictured%20in%20New%20Mexico%2C%20USA.%3Cp%3Evla%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Pentagon%20is%20developing%20AI-enabled%20satellite%20technology.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20satellites%20offer%20advantages%20amid%20intensifying%20competition%20in%20space.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20could%20supercharge%20data%20analysis%20and%20help%20evade%20the%20consequences%20of%20a%20Chinese%20cyber-attack.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20vast%20network%20of%20military%20satellites%20belonging%20to%20the%20US%20has%20long%20underpinned%20its%20dominance%20in%20space.%20But%20China%20is%20challenging%20the%20US%20status%20as%20the%20space%20superpower%2C%20and%20its%20satellite%20system%20is%20in%20the%20crosshairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defensenews.com%2Fspace%2F2025%2F01%2F23%2Fwhy-the-us-navy-wants-to-build-a-fully-autonomous-satellite%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDefense%20News%20reported%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20US%20Navy%20is%20moving%20forward%20with%20plans%20to%20build%20a%20network%20of%20fully%20autonomous%20satellites%20that%20are%20able%20to%20navigate%20independently%20without%20GPS%20or%20ground%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20say%20that%20AI%20could%20help%20the%20US%20stay%20ahead%2C%20providing%20its%20satellites%20with%20the%20capacity%20to%20evade%20the%20consequences%20of%20a%20potentially%20crippling%20attack%2C%20as%20well%20as%20more%20power%20to%20collect%20and%20analyze%20large%20amounts%20of%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22526bcab3-9a33-49be-865b-778353f1e48d%5C%22%3EThe%20race%20for%20satellite%20dominance%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stakes%20in%20the%20battle%20for%20satellite%20supremacy%20are%20high%2C%20Melanie%20Garson%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20in%20International%20Conflict%20Resolution%20%26amp%3B%20International%20Security%20at%20University%20College%20London%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20winner%20would%20control%20a%20vital%20aspect%20of%20space%20infrastructure%2C%20which%20would%20also%20provide%20an%20advantage%20in%20intelligence%20gathering%20and%20precision%20strikes%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20%26quot%3Bwill%20provide%20additional%20capabilities%20for%20surveillance%20and%20espionage%20as%20well%20as%20being%20able%20to%20interfere%20with%20the%20other's%20space%20assets%20through%20spectrum%20warfare%20or%20cyberattacks%2C%26quot%3B%20Garson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20hundreds%20of%20military%20satellites%20in%20orbit%2C%20with%20China%20and%20Russia%20not%20far%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20war%20were%20to%20break%20out%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%2C%20military%20experts%20say%20that%20China%20has%20the%20capability%20to%20do%20serious%20damage%20to%20US%20space-based%20assets%20through%20a%20range%20of%20anti-satellite%2C%20or%20ASAT%2C%20capabilities%2C%20including%20programming%20its%20satellites%20to%20attack%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20CIA%20report%20that%20leaked%20in%202023%20said%20China%20was%20focusing%20its%20efforts%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20war%20on%20hacking%20the%20systems%20used%20to%20control%20US%20satellite%20networks.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESystems%20confrontation%20and%20destruction%20warfare%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20a%20preferred%20Chinese%20military%20tactic%20for%2021st-century%20warfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrippling%20these%20systems%20would%20leave%20satellites%20unable%20to%20transfer%20communications%20and%20data%2C%20or%20even%20coordinate%20with%20each%20other%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e805d22a-33f3-452d-9968-b31a23a9f765%5C%22%3EAI%20could%20be%20the%20key%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20for%20satellites%20could%20be%20crucial%20to%20preserving%20US%20capabilities.%20Unlike%20satellites%20that%20require%20human%20input%2C%20autonomous%20satellites%20can%20operate%20independently%2C%20processing%20and%20analyzing%20data%20to%20make%20their%20own%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20autonomy%20makes%20them%20less%20vulnerable%20to%20possible%20attacks%20on%20bases%20or%20communications%20networks%20or%20to%20being%20cut%20off%20from%20operators%20by%20electronic%20warfare%20like%20signal%20jamming%2C%20said%20Clayton%20Swope%2C%20deputy%20director%20of%20the%20Aerospace%20Security%20Project%20and%20a%20senior%20fellow%20in%20the%20Defense%20and%20Security%20Department%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDecentralized%20decision-making%20may%20add%20resilience%20by%20decreasing%20the%20reliance%20on%20ground-based%20infrastructure%2C%26quot%3B%20Krista%20Langeland%2C%20deputy%20lead%20of%20the%20RAND%20Space%20Enterprise%20Initiative%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAI%20capabilities%20could%20also%20help%20with%20detection%20and%20characterization%20of%20an%20attack.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20advantage%20is%20that%20AI%20could%20help%20process%20vast%20amounts%20of%20data%20in%20space%2C%20and%20identify%20potentially%20hostile%20satellites%20more%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpace%20is%20huge%2C%26quot%3B%20Swope%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20AI%20will%20help%20satellites%20better%20understand%20what's%20happening%20around%20them%20and%20keep%20track%20of%20what%20other%20satellites%20are%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20could%20help%20US%20satellites%20maneuver%20to%20avoid%20accidental%20collisions%20but%20also%20stay%20clear%20of%20potentially%20hostile%20adversarial%20satellites%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e503ffe-06a8-44b8-9dff-6fbb127c1ef5%5C%22%3EA%20distant%20goal%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20power%20of%20the%20technology%20to%20revolutionize%20US%20satellite%20technology%20and%20security%20is%20significant%2C%20Alison%20Grey%2C%20a%20satellites%20expert%20at%20PA%20Consulting%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20AI-enabled%20automation%20can%20enable%20a%20network%20to%20react%20and%20recover%20from%20various%20threats%20in%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhether%20that's%20from%20natural%20phenomena%2C%20anomalies%20in%20one's%20own%20system%2C%20or%20potentially%20hostile%20activity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20while%20the%20technology%20is%20already%20being%20applied%20in%20some%20military%20satellites%2C%20realizing%20its%20full%20potential%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20some%20way%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpace%20Force's%20former%20top%20acquisition%20official%2C%20Frank%20Calvelli%2C%20told%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defenseone.com%2Ftechnology%2F2024%2F08%2Fspace-force-envisions-near-autonomous-satellites-decade-or-so%2F398694%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eevent%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20expects%20satellites%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bsignificantly%20more%20autonomous%26quot%3B%20within%20the%20next%2010%20to%2015%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20efforts%20are%20intensifying%20to%20begin%20realizing%20its%20potential.%20Defense%20News%20said%20that%20the%20US%20Navy%20is%20researching%20a%20fully%20autonomous%20model%2C%20the%20Autosat%2C%20and%20wants%20to%20take%20the%20tests%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20done%20a%20demo%20of%20this%20and%20proven%20out%20the%20principles%20and%20are%20looking%20for%20the%20next%20step%2C%26quot%3B%20Steven%20Meier%2C%20director%20of%20space%20technology%20at%20the%20Naval%20Research%20Laboratory%2C%20said%20at%20a%20recent%20summit%20in%20Virginia.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20get%20funding%20to%20actually%20build%20a%20system%20along%20these%20lines%20and%20launch%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-could-help-us-satellites-evade-crippling-cyber-attack-china-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739701862000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67a5e0657bb3f854015c1f77%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-could-help-us-satellites-evade-crippling-cyber-attack-china-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Pentagon%20is%20developing%20AI-enabled%20satellite%20technology%20that%20could%20supercharge%20data%20analysis%20and%20help%20evade%20the%20consequences%20of%20a%20cyber%20attack.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40busi