r%20destructive%20events%2C%20especially%20as%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethey%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsurance-losses-climate-change-hurricanes-flooding-extreme-weather-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincrease%20in%20frequency%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEach%20disaster%20has%20served%20as%20a%20catalyst%20for%20deeper%20reflection%20and%20adaptation%2C%20and%20this%20continuous%20cycle%20of%20learning%20and%20adjusting%20is%20one%20key%20reason%20why%20Japan%20has%20been%20so%20proactive%20in%20addressing%20disaster%20risk%2C%26quot%3B%20Christian%20Dimmer%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20urban%20studies%20at%20Waseda%20University%20in%20Tokyo%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20major%20seismic%20events%2C%20Japan%20updates%20its%20national%20building%20codes%20based%20on%20what%20it%20learned%20from%20the%20earthquakes.%20Older%20buildings%20quickly%20become%20non-compliant%20and%20less%20attractive%20to%20renters%20and%20buyers%2C%20so%20they're%20often%20torn%20down%20and%20replaced%20with%20safer%20modern%20buildings.%20In%20America%2C%20the%20average%20age%20of%20a%20demolished%20building%20is%2067%20years%2C%20while%20in%20Japan%2C%20it's%2032%2C%20per%20Jiro%20Yoshida%2C%20a%20business%20professor%20at%20Pennsylvania%20State%20University.%20This%20isn't%20just%20a%20result%20of%20building%20code%20reform%3A%20Japan%20lost%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20its%20homes%20during%20World%20War%20II%2C%20and%20those%20that%20were%20rapidly%20built%20to%20replace%20them%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcities%2F2017%2Fnov%2F16%2Fjapan-reusable-housing-revolution%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoften%20poor%20quality%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJapan%20has%20gradually%20cranked%20up%20the%20expectations%20on%20housing%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20Aldrich%2C%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20and%20public%20policy%20at%20Northeastern%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BSo%20a%20house%20built%20in%20the%202020s%20is%20much%20safer%20than%20one%20built%20in%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20than%20one%20built%20in%20the%20'70s%2C%20than%20one%20built%20in%20the%20'50s.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2214f107c7-56b0-4425-964d-56a782043d25%5C%22%3EStrategic%20land-use%20planning%20can%20reduce%20deaths%20and%20destruction%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20construction%20is%20both%20built%20to%20be%20more%20disaster-resistant%20and%20sometimes%20used%20to%20protect%20older%2C%20more%20vulnerable%20buildings.%20In%20one%20such%20case%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.domusweb.it%2Fen%2Farchitecture%2F2024%2F03%2F13%2Fhigashi-shirahige-a-dystopian-prototype-of-the-anti-fire-tokyo-building.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E15-building%20concrete%20Tokyo%20apartment%20complex%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20complete%20with%20steel%20shutters%20and%20a%20sprinkler%20system%2C%20was%20erected%20in%20a%20way%20that%20strategically%20protected%20a%20neighborhood%20of%20mostly%20wooden%20homes%2C%20creating%20a%201.2-kilometer-long%20firewall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Japan%20has%20developed%20various%20land-use%20strategies%20to%20reduce%20casualties%20and%20damage%20from%20earthquakes%2C%20fires%2C%20and%20other%20disasters.%20Officials%20identify%20neighborhoods%20and%20regions%20that%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20and%20create%20firebreaks%20around%20rivers%2C%20railroads%2C%20and%20roadways%20to%20prevent%20fires%20from%20jumping%20from%20one%20area%20to%20another%2C%20Dimmer%20said.%20Cities%20have%20created%20new%20greenspaces%2C%20including%20pocket%20parks%20featuring%20emergency%20water%20stores%20and%20rations%2C%20widened%20some%20of%20their%20extremely%20narrow%20streets%2C%20and%20phased%20out%20dead-end%20streets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20stands%20out%20in%20Japan's%20approach%20is%20the%20institutionalized%20mechanism%20of%20learning%20from%20disasters%20and%20translating%20those%20lessons%20into%20concrete%2C%20actionable%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20Dimmer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Great%20Kanto%20Earthquake%20of%201923%2C%20which%20also%20triggered%20massive%20fires%20and%20a%20major%20tsunami%20that%20devastated%20Tokyo%20and%20Yokohama%2C%20the%20country%20learned%20that%20green%20spaces%20are%20critical%20fire%20breaks%20and%20to%20act%20as%20evacuation%20zones%2C%20Dimmer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20wake%20of%20Japan's%202011%20earthquake%2C%20tsunami%2C%20and%20nuclear%20accident%2C%20the%20country%20invested%20in%20coastal%20infrastructure%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fworld%2Fseven-years-after-tsunami-japanese-live-uneasily-with-seawalls-idUSKCN1GL0D8%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassive%20seawalls%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20relocated%20residents%20out%20of%20particularly%20vulnerable%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20efforts%20to%20bring%20people%20closer%20to%20the%20city%20centers%2C%20reduce%20sprawl%2C%20and%20then%20also%20if%20you%20have%20built%20in%20a%20place%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20have%20built%20or%20is%20deemed%20unsafe%2C%20then%20there%20are%20subsidies%20to%20help%20you%20move%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Miho%20Mazereeuw%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20architecture%20and%20director%20of%20the%20Urban%20Risk%20Lab%20at%20MIT%20who's%20writing%20a%20book%20entitled%20%26quot%3BDesign%20Before%20Disaster%3A%20Japan's%20Culture%20of%20Preparedness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227d451bf0-975b-4c1a-bf6a-a5c30b1c19cd%5C%22%3EA%20'culture%20of%20preparedness'%20braces%20residents%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Japan%2C%20schoolchildren%20are%20required%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eparticipate%20in%20regular%20earthquake%2C%20fire%2C%20typhoon%2C%20and%20other%20disaster%20preparedness%20drills.%20They%20study%20evacuation%20routes%20and%20learn%20how%20to%20take%20cover%20depending%20on%20the%20emergency.%20They%20also%20memorize%20a%20famous%20phrase%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20push%2C%20don't%20run%2C%20don't%20speak%2C%20and%20don't%20go%20back.%26quot%3B%20But%20it's%20not%20just%20kids%20who%20are%20trained%20%E2%80%94%20residents%20of%20all%20ages%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feastasiaforum.org%2F2024%2F08%2F20%2Fwhat-japan-can-teach-the-world-about-disaster-risk-reduction%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DJapan%252C%2520despite%2520having%2520high%2520exposure%2Cenhance%2520their%2520resilience%2520against%2520disasters.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeducated%20in%20disaster%20response%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%2C%20in%202015%2C%20the%20Tokyo%20Metropolitan%20Government%20produced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.japantimes.co.jp%2Fculture%2F2015%2F11%2F07%2Fbooks%2Fbook-reviews%2Fguide-disaster-survival-good-design%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20post-disaster%20survival%20manual%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EBosai%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20this%20culture%20of%20preparedness%20that's%20been%20ingrained%20in%20every%20level%20of%20society%2C%20from%20what%20children%20are%20taught%20in%20schools%2C%20to%20organizations%20that%20are%20community-level%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mazereeuw.%20Communities%20are%20asked%20%26quot%3Bto%20really%20think%20through%20both%20the%20city%20design%20and%20then%20also%20how%20the%20community%20members%20interact%20with%20each%20other%2C%20support%20each%20other%20through%20these%20kinds%20of%20events.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimmer%20said%20this%20culture%20is%20based%20on%20the%20understanding%20that%20building%20a%20more%20disaster-resilient%20society%20requires%20collective%20action%20and%20major%20investments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAdequate%20financial%20resources%2C%20building%20civic%20structures%2C%20and%20empowering%20individuals%20to%20exercise%20foresight%20are%20crucial%2C%26quot%3B%20Dimmer%20added.%20%26quot%3BEqually%20important%2C%20however%2C%20is%20addressing%20the%20underlying%20cultural%20mindset%20that%20views%20these%20efforts%20as%20essential%20for%20the%20greater%20good%2C%20rather%20than%20seeing%20them%20as%20burdensome%20or%20unnecessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229fa088e6-e08f-479d-a19d-9b91ac5881f4%5C%22%3EBuilding%20more%20resilient%20structures%20can%20keep%20people%20safe%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20officials%20in%20Japan%20have%20worked%20to%20keep%20people%20safe%20from%20disasters%20like%20tsunamis%20and%20volcanoes%20by%20consistently%20pushing%20construction%20firms%20to%20improve%20resiliency.%20And%20so%20far%2C%20it's%20been%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%207.5%20magnitude%20earthquake%20struck%20the%20Noto%20Peninsula%20in%20the%20central%20prefecture%20of%20Ishikawa%2C%20Japan%2C%20in%20January%202024%2C%20at%20least%2057%20people%20were%20killed%20and%20hundreds%20of%20homes%20were%20destroyed.%20Robert%20Geller%2C%20professor%20emeritus%20of%20seismology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Tokyo%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2024%2F01%2F06%2Fstyle%2Fjapan-earthquake-architecture-dfi-hnk%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20CNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20modern%20buildings%20fared%20better%20than%20older%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%207.8%20magnitude%20earthquake%20struck%20Kahramanmaras%2C%20Turkey%20in%20February%202023%2C%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdisasterphilanthropy.org%2Fdisasters%2F2023-turkey-syria-earthquake%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAt%2520least%2520230%252C000%2520buildings%2520were%2Cbuildings%2520were%2520classified%2520as%2520unsafe.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E230%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20buildings%20were%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%2C%20and%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2023%2F02%2F10%2Fworld%2Fmiddleeast%2Fkahramanmaras-turkey-earthquake-damage.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUsing%2520satellite%2520imagery%252C%2520The%2520Times%2Ccenter%2520had%2520less%2520apparent%2520destruction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E4%2C800%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20died.%20Damage%20from%20earthquakes%20can%20vary%20significantly%20depending%20on%20where%20they%20occur%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20compare%20two%20events.%20However%2C%20experts%20told%20BI%20that%20Japan's%20resiliency%20measures%20have%20helped%20the%20country%20reduce%20building%20damage%20and%20save%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20Japan's%20approach%20to%20disasters%20isn't%20foolproof.%20Big%20earthquakes%20in%20recent%20decades%20have%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%20many%20buildings%20and%20had%20high%20death%20tolls.%20There%20are%20also%20high%20environmental%20costs%20of%20tearing%20down%20older%20structures%20and%20rebuilding%20as%20much%20as%20Japan%20does%2C%20such%20as%20creating%20significant%20carbon%20emissions%20and%20waste%20that%20can%20be%20detrimental%20to%20the%20environment.%20There%20are%20also%20cultural%20costs.%20Many%20older%2C%20often%20wooden%20buildings%20in%20Japan%20have%20been%20demolished%20in%20order%20to%20rebuild%20more%20disaster-resilient%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20course%2C%20I%20believe%20in%20human%20safety%20being%20the%20most%20important%20thing%2C%20but%20I%20lament%20a%20bit%20the%20loss%20of%20many%20more%20traditional%20homes%2C%26quot%3B%20Mazereeuw%20said%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eadding%20that%20she%20hopes%20buildings%20can%20begin%20to%20be%20retrofitted%20more%20frequently%20rather%20than%20torn%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAldrich%20said%20the%20US%20may%20struggle%20with%20this%20strategy%20without%20first%20reforming%20its%20%26quot%3Bpatchwork%26quot%3B%20building%20codes%20that%20are%20different%20across%20cities%20and%20states.%20In%20comparison%2C%20he%20said%20Japan's%20national%20government%20has%20made%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2Finteractive%2F2019%2F06%2F03%2Fus%2Fearthquake-preparedness-usa-japan.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanges%20to%20building%20codes%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20apply%20to%20the%20entire%20country%2C%20a%20model%20that%20he%20said%20the%20US%20should%20take%20some%20lessons%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20should%20work%20to%20create%20updated%20federal%20standards%20for%20designing%20built%20structures%20%E2%80%94%20both%20residential%20and%20commercial%20%E2%80%94%20that%20can%20withstand%20floods%20and%20fires%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-disaster-resilient-construction-american-can-learn-building-code-culture-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739696462000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ace59f7bb3f854015caa2e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-disaster-resilient-construction-american-can-learn-building-code-culture-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Japan%20has%20spent%20decades%20making%20its%20buildings%20more%20resilient%20to%20earthquakes.%20Similar%20changes%20could%20be%20difficult%20for%20the%20US%20to%20implement.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman%2CJacob%20Zinkula)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-disaster-resilient-construction-american-can-learn-building-code-culture-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Independent%20Production%20on%20the%20Rise%2C%20Studios%20Cut%20Back%20and%20Everyone%20Looks%20to%20Asia%3A%20Takeaways%20From%20Ampere%20Analysis%E2%80%99%20EFM%20Presentation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739696400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FBerlin-EFM.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236309292%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20enterta